/uczeris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czeris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:20:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sweetest RvR Kills</span><hr size=1> I would love to hear your stories.  I am sure that one or two kills in RvR have been that much sweeter for you, because you did it as an assassin, or for whatever other reason.<br><br>Post 'em here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uczeris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czeris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:28:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sweetest RvR Kills</span><hr size=1> I'll post my new favourite, from last night btw.  <br><br>A bunch of Mids are camping at the albion milefort in Emain.  They have complete control of it, with about 20 people there.  I am of course watching, ineffectually from the sidelines, unable to do anything.<br><br>So what do I see, but a nice yellow con norsewoman in chain (no idea the class, healer maybe?) named Eveshka go into the upper gatehouse.  She does not emerge for a couple minutes, so I decide to go in as well.  This is not normally a good idea, as when people see doors opening, that usually means you are dead. But what the hell.<br><br>I go in and find her standing in the window of the upper gatehouse, facing outwards towards the rest of the Mids below, healing them and /waving, etc.<br><br>So I stand right behind her, knowing that she has to turn around eventually.  5 minutes of standing there, and she finally turns.  PA/CD/SS took her to about 1/2 health.  She kind of freaks a bit, tries to escape, realizes there's closed doors in the way (while I am hitting her) then /bows before she dies.<br><br>Her friends are now on the way, but I jump out of the window and stealth away.<br><br>Best RvR kill for me, just because of the situation, and the uniqueness of it.  It actually *felt* like an assassination.<br><br>Czeris<br>43 Nightshade<br>Gawaine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udragonstylez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DragonStylez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:33:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sweetest RvR Kills</span><hr size=1> Great Work!  <br><br>It would be an honor being on your end of the blade, and to be taken down that way <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwoodydarogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WoodyDaRogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:36:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nice!</span><hr size=1> Very nice kill. I tend to avoid those nasty healers, i hate instas.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unarezza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>narezza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:46:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cracked me up...</span><hr size=1> <br>This one happened to me just last night as well...<br><br>I was running south from my gate to the Albion gate in Midgard (Odin's). I was cutting through the woods southward, almost to the road when I spot a bunch of corpses on the road. So I stroll out to investigate (hidden obviously) and see 3 dead Albions and one dead Hibernian. Just for a split second I see a hidden Briton invader (Archer) but not I'm not quick enough to check con. So I run around in hide some more to spot him and I catch a few more glimpses of him but nothing solid. At this point I'm thinking he is definitly too high a level for me to kill and decide I should run. Next thing I know he pops out of hide. I believe this was because he was being cocky and thought this little shrimp Lurikeen couldn't touch him (He was red con). So at this point I'm still about to run, but just then I see an undead aggroing him from behind! So he starts to run away with this undead after him, he gets diseased and I chase him down and catch him easily as he has majorly slowed down. I catch him and melee him to death with the help of the zombie!!! (I almost died too, 5-10% health left)<br><br>I was laughing so hard after that, and noticed he /released REAL fast. I'm not sure if the zombie did more damage to him than I did, but if so he also lost xp. I'm still not sure if he came out of hide because he was being cocky and was trying to mess with me, or because the undead behind him popped him out of it, either way I'm damn satisfied with the results. I personally would never purposely grief kill someone, but this situation was just too good to pass up. Especially because he was red con to me =)<br><br>Narezza<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hansle>hansle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:50:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1>  i was watching what looked like a guild meeting outside of uppland. there was a little grey guy running around the out skirts o the group of about 15. i thought why not so i hit him. right in front of his own guild he dropped dead and i walked away still stealthed only to leave them pisssed as they have ever been. it's not that exicting but sure was funny.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usneekeerz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sneekeerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 1:28:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> Well, once there was this big fight between Albions and Hibernia at Odins Gate at Hibernia's milefort. I was stealthed waiting for the 'right' target to strike, while my realm mates are hacking it out. The I saw an orange con Lurikeen on top of the gate raining down arrows on our clerics.<br>So I decided to sneak up and beat the crapo outta him. He was facing the arrow slits on the wall so there was no way I could land my PA. So I waved at him twice when I was right beside him stealthed. He fell for it, got his weapon out and faced me. Poked me once, and I replied with a huge PA(this was before the stealth nerf). Enervating resisted, but no biggie. Naturally, I followed up with Creeping Death. Then I hear 'thunk', it was blocked! There geos my stun. I was kinda suprised cuz that was the first for me fighting a ranger with a shield. We duked it out for about 15 secs, and I was loosing...<br>The ranger was at around 25% health, but I was down to 10%. Then...I saw the arrow slit(window) on the wall. I said screw this, time ta getta hell outta ere. I disengaged and ran for the window, and jumped down. Yay safe fall! But the ranger had no such luck! The fool was so battle frenzy that he jumped with me and ... SPLAT on the floor. 500+ rp from that guy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 1:30:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> Best for me was last night as well (last night seems to have been a good RvR evening for most hehe).<br><br>Me and a friend finished getting him level 40 in the frontier, so we decide to run around emain and if we didn't see anyone we'd suicide and call it a night.<br><br>We run to albion portal fort and since he's a bard, we're running around with speedy-feet like idiots.  We get flanked by some albions, but end up killing them (I died in the process, but we as a group prevailed).  While dead I go LD and end up at bind point.  I come back and he suicides and we run back out for round two.<br><br>This time we pick up a friend to join us, and all three of us run out for a rematch (cause we KNOW they'll be back).  Stupid us, they setup bait (a low blue running around by himself) and we fell for it, when we attacked him they ran up and killed us.  It was horrible.  This was my second death to a theurgist (damn their pets hit HARD) btw, important later.<br><br>Not to be outdone, round three.  We run out again to the albion milefort, I'm running ahead scouting, stealthed.  I go up the alb milefort stairs, check the upper room, leap out the window, do a quick perimeter check for stealthers, see nothing and tell them to head through.   DOH, albions setup an ambush between the two doors.  I didn't want to give us away by opening the door so I never checked there.  I'm stupid!   Anyway, we prevail and the albs release, sure to come back.<br><br>We setup at the milefort waiting for them.  And we wait.  And wait.  I scout the portal fort a few times .. nothing.  So I suggest to the group that we run to the portal fort .. but approach it from the aggro-monster side, surely a stupid move that they wouldn't expect hehe.  I have the group wait out of sight and I scout the portal fort from the wrong side.  Hey look a big group of albions are heading out to the milefort, AND THEY DIDN'T SEE US, WOOO.<br><br>Group and myself run up behind them while they're staring at the milefort picking their arses, and slaughter them.<br><br>Here's the REALLY good part though.  The theurgist that had killed me twice earlier was mezzed.  I sneak up and perf him.  Success!  But he quickcasts AE mez and starts to run off with very low health.  He got lucky and caught us ALL in the mez ... he's getting away!<br><br>Enter bleed damage.  6 pts .. 5 pts ... 4 pts, and he keels over dead.<br><br>Haha =) <p>-- Huff McTuff, 40 Nightshade, Pendragon<br>-- <i>Nightshade Team Lead</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaaxtherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaax the Rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 4:26:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> Very nice stories.... I have one to add.<br><br>I was hunting in the Hibernian Gorge all night, getting some decent Realm Points. Me and my associate Infiltrator friend were just about to call it a night.... when he (the lookout) calls out from ahead that there's an Orange caster heading my way. Ripre (the other assasin) was closer to the Hibernian Gates, while I was down the road a bit. <br>I look up,and spot the caster.. I position myself dead centre infront of him.. he's running (with a pet in tow) straight for me, at full speed.. comming, comming, COMMING......<br><br>Then, all of a sudden, PERF ART! One shot, DOWN, on the DEAD RUN! Nothing, and I mean, NOTHING has given me more satisfaction then than taking down that orange (worth about 400+ if I recall) in one shot, AND On the dead RUN!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Try that in your spare time.<br><br>Jaax. <p><img src="http://www.flavonsen.com/images/jaax-new2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valaface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> My favorite kill wasn't particularly hard, or spectacular, or daring, but it's my favorite for two reasons: no other class my level –- except a Ranger -- could have done this, and it caused an even-con party to flee in terror.<br><br>I was by myself near the Midgard Mile Fort in Emain Macha, and I noticed a party of four Mids resting near the top of a hill at the zone wall: a yellow troll, a yellow norsewoman, a yellow dwarf, and a green kobold with a bow.  I didn't see what they were resting from, but the troll was wounded and sitting. I identified the troll as their only tank (thank you Quid Pro Quo Thread), and went for him instead of the easy one-shot (Kobold).  The sound of weapons being drawn followed immediately by a death cry is the sweetest sound in the Universe.  Still hidden, I immediately turned down the hill (faster than backpedaling) and walked a few steps to get out of &quot;detect range&quot; from the others.  When I turned around to engage my next target, all three were hightailing it east towards the portal fort. <p><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valarauco.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufandangodarkdance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandango Darkdance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:30:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> My sweetest kill was as follows.<br><br>I was in mount collory when I found a group fighting purple mobs cant recall what they were. The group was having a verry hard time and were yellow to me with only one healer. I waited for a pull and attacked the healer, I was killed tho the healer was also killed. The mob finishd off the entire group wich made the kill sweet. I just wish that I could have talked to them, woulda let them know no hard feelings just making a point to mythic.<br><br>I belive in the exp death till we are finishd and can acttualy be assasins.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 6:13:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe this one was just rude</span><hr size=1> My favorite one was when my group and I were hunting in Yggdra forest.  I was out scouting ahead when the group was taken from behind and all were killed. I saw them dying and headed back, only to get there as the last person was killed.<br><br>The group of Mids were all red/purple to me, except for one green troll, and when they were done, they all went their separate ways, except for the troll, who stayed behind to be a gentleman and bow to my dead party-mates.  I moved in, and on his last bow, PA'd him in mid-bow, and then proceeded to solo him to death.<br><br>Unfortuneately there was a scout nearby and he made short work of me, but the rest of my party was most appreciative.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyall</A> at: 2/6/02 6:13:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaiyasamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maiya Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 6:44:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The many deaths of Leria...</span><hr size=1> There's a Norsewoman caster on Percival whom I've killed many times all because of an incident involving a nearly-killed-by-me kobold archer and her staff...<br><br>The first night, after getting ressed, I wandered about Emain Macha for hours looking just for her. I cannot fully describe how upset I was to die by the staff of a caster. Probably because her staff hit me for around 170.<br><br>So, I spot her chain AE nuking some Hibbies, who being the clumsy disorganized and self-centered lot that Percival Hibbies are, run around in circles while she racks up the RPs. Now, she's surrounded by all manners of healers and tanks, but I'm looking for revenge at any cost, so I strike. Perf, Creeping Death, and start stabbing.<br><br>Now, being the smart cookie that I am, I use disease poison almost always. It proved to be a very good time to disease Leria, because the dwarf standing next to her pops an insta-heal on her. Garrote... Achilles' Heel... finally she dies and I sprint.<br><br>Now, to this day, I'll never understand it, I get away (literally with murder). I make it back to the Albion Milewall and rest for a bit. About a half hour later, what do I see, but Leria running down the path from the Middy wall to the Albion wall. Now, for a moment, my conscious says: <i>Jalena, you've taken your revenge.</i> To which the conscious with horns replies: <i>She beat you to death with a stick! More revenge is required!</i><br><br>So I sneak onto the path, and perf just as she crosses my Mulmar-Kadaffy-esque Line of Death. I slam her with a Creeping Death, and this time finish her off and make a get away again.<br><br>Now, you'd think this would be the end of the story... but oh no... the very next day in the Albion Frontier she died twice to my blades. But it doesn't end there... the next few days I headed deep into Midgard to see about terrorizing the little ones (which turns out is about as much fun as shooting fish in a barrel). Low-and-behold! Leria running straight towards me... not even on a path. I step up to the plate, wind-up, swing... BLAM! 270ish perf with a 260ish crit! One-hit!<br><br>Now, it's been said that back in real life there was a silly woman staring at the computer who emitted a sound that was not unlike a squeal of delight.<br><br>The moral of the story is... don't kill Jalena with a stick unless you are a briton wearing a brown robe. She takes it very personal.<br> <p><p style="text-align: right; font-size: 80%; font-family: Verdana">Jalena! Nightshade of Percival<br><i>Danger calls; it intoxicates. Beyond the walls real excitement waits.<br>Adreneline rush--dance along the ledge. Forbidden touch--kiss the razor's edge.</i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquizy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squizy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 9:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2042.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LOL</span><hr size=1> So I came on at least 20 middys at the zombie/wisp area ( an unusually high number for Yggdra <!--